# Prisma Design System Component Rules

## Core Principles

This project is built exclusively with the **Prisma Design System**. All UI components, styling, and patterns must come from the Prisma design system packages.

## CRITICAL: Correct Theme Provider Usage

### âś… ALWAYS Use PrismaThemeProvider with a Theme Object


import {
  PrismaThemeProvider,
  themes,
  Button,
  Heading,
  Body,
  Card,
  Box,
  Flex,
} from '@edreamsodigeo/prisma-design-system';

export default function MyPage() {
  return (
    <PrismaThemeProvider theme={themes.COBALT_ED}>
      {/* Your components here */}
    </PrismaThemeProvider>
  );
}
```

### âťŚ NEVER Use These (Incorrect)

```tsx
// âťŚ Wrong - causes theme error
<PrismaProvider>

// âťŚ Wrong - causes theme error  
<CobaltProvider>

// âťŚ Wrong - causes theme error
<DiamondProvider>
```

### Available Themes

Use one of these theme objects with `PrismaThemeProvider`:
- `themes.COBALT_ED` - eDreams Cobalt theme (recommended)
- `themes.COBALT_GO` - Go Voyages Cobalt theme
- `themes.COBALT_OP` - Opodo Cobalt theme
- `themes.COBALT_TR` - Travellink Cobalt theme
- `themes.DIAMOND_ED` - eDreams Diamond theme
- `themes.DIAMOND_GO` - Go Voyages Diamond theme
- `themes.DIAMOND_OP` - Opodo Diamond theme
- `themes.DIAMOND_TR` - Travellink Diamond theme

## Typography Components

### âś… ALWAYS Use Prisma Typography Components

```tsx
// âś… Correct - use Heading component
<Heading level={1}>My Title</Heading>
<Heading level={2}>Subtitle</Heading>
<Heading level={3}>Section Title</Heading>

// âś… Correct - use Body component
<Body size="large">Large body text</Body>
<Body>Normal body text</Body>
<Body size="small">Small body text</Body>
<Body weight="bold">Bold text</Body>
```

### âťŚ NEVER Use HTML Elements for Typography

```tsx
// âťŚ Wrong - don't use HTML heading tags
<h1>My Title</h1>
<h2>Subtitle</h2>
<h3>Section Title</h3>

// âťŚ Wrong - don't use HTML p tags
<p>Some text</p>

// âťŚ Wrong - don't use span with inline styles
<span style={{ fontSize: '14px', fontWeight: 600 }}>Text</span>
```

## Component Usage

### Always Use Prisma Components

1. **Never create custom UI components** when a Prisma component exists
2. **Always import from Prisma packages** for:
   - Buttons (`Button` component with variants: primary, secondary, text, positive, warning, critical)
   - Forms (inputs, selects, checkboxes, radio buttons, etc.)
   - Navigation (headers, footers, menus, tabs, breadcrumbs)
   - Layout components (`Box`, `Flex`, `FlexRow`, `Col` for grid)
   - Typography (`Heading`, `Body`, `Display`, `Typography`)
   - Cards (`Card`, `HighlightedCard`)
   - Modals and dialogs (`Modal`, `Popup`, `Drawer`)
   - Tooltips and popovers (`Tooltip`, `Popover`)
   - Tables (`Table`, `TableBody`, `TableCell`, `TableHead`, `TableHeader`, `TableRow`)
   - Loading states (`Spinner`, `SkeletonButton`, `SkeletonBox`)
   - Icons (`Icon` component)
   - Alerts and notifications (`Alert`, `Message`, `MessageBox`)
   - Badges and tags (`Badge`)
   - Any other UI elements

3. **Check Prisma documentation first** before building any component
4. **Custom components are only allowed** for:
   - Business logic specific to this application
   - Complex compositions of Prisma components
   - Components that genuinely don't exist in the design system

### Correct Component Imports

```tsx
import {
  // Theme
  PrismaThemeProvider,
  themes,
  
  // Layout
  Box,
  Flex,
  FlexRow,
  Col,
  
  // Typography
  Heading,
  Body,
  Display,
  Typography,
  
  // Components
  Button,
  Card,
  Badge,
  Icon,
  Input,
  Select,
  Checkbox,
  RadioButton,
  Modal,
  Tooltip,
  Alert,
  Spinner,
} from '@edreamsodigeo/prisma-design-system';
```

## Styling Rules

### Use Prisma's sx Prop for Styling

Prisma components use the `sx` prop for styling (Emotion/styled-system):

```tsx
<Box
  sx={{
    padding: '24px',
    margin: '16px',
    backgroundColor: '#f0f0f0',
  }}
>
  Content
</Box>
```

### Custom CSS Only When Necessary

1. **Prefer Prisma components and sx prop** over custom CSS
2. **Use Prisma's layout system** (`Box`, `Flex`, etc.)
3. **Custom CSS only for**:
   - Application-specific layouts
   - Animations not provided by Prisma
   - Edge cases not covered by the design system

## Code Standards

### Imports

```tsx
// âś… Correct - import from Prisma
import { 
  Button, 
  PrismaThemeProvider,
  themes,
  Heading,
  Body 
} from '@edreamsodigeo/prisma-design-system';

// âťŚ Incorrect - don't create custom versions
import { Button } from '@/components/Button';
```

### TypeScript

1. Use Prisma's TypeScript types for component props
2. Import types from Prisma packages:
   ```tsx
   import type { ButtonProps, HeadingProps, BodyProps } from '@edreamsodigeo/prisma-design-system';
   ```

## Complete Example

```tsx
'use client';

import {
  PrismaThemeProvider,
  themes,
  Box,
  Flex,
  Card,
  Button,
  Heading,
  Body,
  Badge,
} from '@edreamsodigeo/prisma-design-system';
import Link from 'next/link';

export default function MyPage() {
  return (
    <PrismaThemeProvider theme={themes.COBALT_ED}>
      <Box
        sx={{
          minHeight: '100vh',
          padding: '24px',
        }}
      >
        <Heading level={1} sx={{ marginBottom: '16px' }}>
          Page Title
        </Heading>
        
        <Body size="large" sx={{ marginBottom: '32px' }}>
          This is a description of the page using Body component.
        </Body>

        <Flex sx={{ gap: '16px', marginBottom: '32px' }}>
          <Button variant="primary">Primary Action</Button>
          <Button variant="secondary">Secondary Action</Button>
        </Flex>

        <Card sx={{ padding: '24px' }}>
          <Heading level={3} sx={{ marginBottom: '12px' }}>
            Card Title
          </Heading>
          <Body>
            Card content goes here using the Body component.
          </Body>
        </Card>
      </Box>
    </PrismaThemeProvider>
  );
}
```

## Validation Checklist

Before submitting any work, verify:

- [ ] Using `PrismaThemeProvider` with `themes.COBALT_ED` (or another theme)
- [ ] All headings use `Heading` component (not h1, h2, h3 tags)
- [ ] All body text uses `Body` component (not p or span tags)
- [ ] All buttons use `Button` component with proper variants
- [ ] Layout uses `Box`, `Flex`, `FlexRow` from Prisma
- [ ] No custom UI components that duplicate Prisma functionality
- [ ] TypeScript types imported from Prisma packages
- [ ] Custom styles are minimal and only for application-specific needs

## When in Doubt

1. **Search Prisma documentation** first
2. **Check available exports** from `@edreamsodigeo/prisma-design-system`
3. **Ask the user** which Prisma component to use
4. **Prefer composition** over creation
5. **Think "assemble" not "build"** - we're assembling Prisma components

---

**Remember**: This is a Prisma Design System project. The goal is to showcase and use Prisma components correctly, not to create custom UI.
